    <field name="note"><![CDATA[<h1><strong>Wine Sensory Evaluation Template</strong></h1><h2><strong>1. Appearance</strong></h2><table class="table table-bordered"><thead><tr><th>Attribute</th><th>Score (0–5)</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Color intensity</td><td>4</td><td>Deep ruby, good saturation</td></tr><tr><td>Hue / rim variation</td><td>3</td><td>Slight garnet edges, expected for age-worthy style</td></tr><tr><td>Clarity / brilliance</td><td>5</td><td>Clear, no haze</td></tr></tbody></table><h2><strong>2. Nose / Aroma</strong></h2><table class="table table-bordered"><thead><tr><th>Attribute</th><th>Score (0–5)</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Red fruit</td><td>4</td><td>Cherry, raspberry prominent</td></tr><tr><td>Dark fruit</td><td>3</td><td>Plum undertones from Malbec</td></tr><tr><td>Floral / herb</td><td>4</td><td>Peppery and herbal notes from Cab Franc</td></tr><tr><td>Spice / pepper</td><td>4</td><td>Matches blend style</td></tr><tr><td>Oak / vanilla / toast</td><td>2</td><td>Subtle hint, can be enhanced in barrel aging</td></tr><tr><td>Other descriptors</td><td>–</td><td>Slight graphite note, adds complexity</td></tr></tbody></table><h2><strong>3. Palate / Taste</strong></h2><table class="table table-bordered"><thead><tr><th>Attribute</th><th>Score (0–5)</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Acidity / freshness</td><td>4</td><td>Fresh, balanced; aligns with blend target</td></tr><tr><td>Tannin / structure</td><td>4</td><td>Firm, slightly astringent; may benefit from slight softening</td></tr><tr><td>Body / mouthfeel</td><td>4</td><td>Medium to full-bodied, well-rounded</td></tr><tr><td>Fruit expression</td><td>3</td><td>Bright, but Syrah/Malbec integration could be improved</td></tr><tr><td>Balance / harmony</td><td>4</td><td>Overall well-structured, minor tweaks suggested</td></tr><tr><td>Finish / length</td><td>3</td><td>Moderate length; could be extended with more structure or blending tweaks</td></tr></tbody></table><h2><strong>4. Overall Impression</strong></h2><table class="table table-bordered"><thead><tr><th>Attribute</th><th>Score (0–5)</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Overall quality</td><td>4</td><td>High quality, meets style expectations</td></tr><tr><td>Style match (vs target)</td><td>3</td><td>Slightly austere; could be fruitier for broader appeal</td></tr><tr><td>Aging potential</td><td>4</td><td>Good, suitable for medium to long-term aging</td></tr></tbody></table><h2><strong>5. Key Takeaways / Iteration Notes</strong></h2><ol>
<li><p><strong>Adjust tannin / structure:</strong> Slightly reduce Cab Franc proportion or adjust maceration to soften astringency.</p></li>
<li><p><strong>Modify fruit balance:<font style="color: rgb(0, 0, 255);"> Increase Syrah or Malbec fraction</font></strong> for rounder mid-palate and darker fruit perception.</p></li>
<li><p><strong>Aroma / complexity tweaks:</strong> Consider blending in a small portion of riper grapes or barrel-aged fraction to add depth.</p></li>
<li><p><strong>Acidity / sweetness adjustments:</strong> Fine as-is; no adjustment needed.</p></li>
<li><p><strong>Maturation / oak recommendations:</strong> Medium oak aging recommended to integrate tannins and enhance finish.</p></li></ol>]]></field>
